article_title: Woman Hit By Light Rail Train
article_text:
Credit: KCNC

A woman suffered unspecified injuries after she was hit by a light rail train Saturday morning.

Lone Tree police didn't offer many details about the accident, but confirmed it happened just after 10 a.m. at the Lincoln light rail station. The woman, who is in her 70s, was walking across the tracks.

The accident remains under investigation. No further information has been made available at this time.
